      <small>Story</small><br>
      French DCRI Case<br>
      <small>March 2013</small>
    </h3>
    <hr />
    <p>In March 2013, a French intelligence agency called the DCRI detained a French Wikipedia user and threatened him with severe criminal penalties if he did not use his administrative rights to delete from French Wikipedia information about a military base that the DCRI deemed classified. The supposedly classified information was actually publicly available because the military had provided interviews and a tour of the base to local reporters. We defended the Wikipedia user involved and fought to keep the content up on French Wikipedia. Read more.</p>
