    <h3>
      <small>Story</small><br>
      Monkey Picture<br>
      <small>January 2014</small>
    </h3>
    <hr />
    <p>In July 2011, an award-winning photographer left his camera unattended in a national park in North Sulawesi, Indonesia. A female crested black macaque monkey got ahold of the camera and took a series of pictures, including some self-portraits. The pictures were featured in an online newspaper article and eventually posted to Commons. We received a takedown request in January 2014 based on the argument that the photographer owned the copyright to the photographs. Believing that the photographs are in the public domain, we denied the request.</p>
